column4: Rank
column6:
Entry Standards
                            
                            
                                Entry Standards
                                The average UCAS tariff score of new students entering the University. These tables use the old UCAS tariff.
                                Read more
column7:
Student Satisfaction
                            
                            
                                Student Satisfaction
                                A guide to how satisfied students are with the quality of teaching they receive.
                                    Maximum score: 5.00
                                Read more
column8:
Research Quality
                            
                            
                                Research Quality
                                A measure of the quality of the research undertaken in the University.
                                    Maximum score: 4.00
                                Read more
column9:
Research Intensity
                            
                            
                                Research Intensity
                                A measure of the proportion of staff involved in high-quality research in the University.
                                    Maximum score: 1.00
                                Read more
column10:
Graduate Prospects
                            
                            
                                Graduate Prospects
                                A guide to the employability of graduates on completion of their courses at the University.
                                    Maximum score: 100.0
                                Read more
column11:
Student-Staff Ratio
                            
                            
                                Student-Staff Ratio
                                The average staffing levels at the University.
                                Read more
column12:
Academic Services Spend
                            
                            
                                Academic Services Spend
                                A guide to how much the University spends on supporting services such as libraries and IT.
                                Read more
column13:
Facilities Spend
                            
                            
                                Facilities Spend
                                A guide to how much the University spends on supporting facilities such as the careers service, health and counselling services and sport facilities.
                                Read more
column14:
Good Honours
                            
                            
                                Good Honours
                                The percentage of graduates achieving a first or upper second class honours degree – the class of degree achieved can impact a graduate’s employment prospects.
                                    Maximum score: 100.0
                                Read more
column15:
Degree Completion
                            
                            
                                Degree Completion
                                The proportion of students expected to successfully complete their studies and gain a degree from the University.
                                    Maximum score: 100.0
                                Read more
column16:
Overall Score
                            
                            
                                Overall Score
                                The total score calculated by our independent and trusted methodology, comprising entry standards, student satisfaction, research assessment (quality and intensity), graduate prospects, student–staff ratio, academic services spend, facilities spend, good honours, and degree completion.
                                    Maximum score: 1000
                                Read more
